ion, including no silent-drop state loss.","test_description":"Submit clean multimodal posts through the real moderation pipeline, verify both model stages return pass, and assert final state is published (not held, not dropped) with persisted audit trail.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.14,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.22,"Workflow":0.6}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The full moderation pipeline — image check, text check, publish decision — completes within 5 seconds of submission.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Provisional pick: System due real latency boundary; upgraded to Workflow after re-check because the SLO is for multiple real agentic steps in sequence. Mocked models hide true timing/failure interactions under peak throughput.","test_description":"Load-test end-to-end submissions against real models and production-like infrastructure; measure p95/p99 completion from submit to decision and assert the pipeline stays within 5 seconds.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.02,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.18,"Workflow":0.7}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the AI vision model is unavailable, image posts are queued for retry rather than auto-approved.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Provisional pick: Integration because the failure boundary is module handoff (vision-client error -> moderation decision -> retry queue write). Re-check against System: behavior text only requires handling unavailability state, which can be reproduced with an in-process client stub emitting timeout/503 errors; no OS/network primitive is required. Re-check against Agentic: it does not depend on model output quality, only failure-path orchestration.","test_description":"Wire moderation service, vision client adapter, and retry queue in-process; force adapter unavailability errors and assert posts are enqueued for retry and n